Family and friends mourned the deaths of children gunned down Tuesday
at Cleveland Elementary School in Stockton, CA. The burial of Patrick
Purdy, 24, who opened fire during recess with an AK-47 semiautomatic
assault rifle, killing five children and wounding 29 others, went
nearly unnoticed. Fourteen wounded are still hospitalized.
Three-quarters of the school's 970 students returned to classes by
Friday, with some parents sitting in with children. Cleveland School
is in California's third-largest community of Southeast Asian
refugees. All the dead and 19 of the wounded were from refugee
families. Authorities denied a racial motive in the attack, claiming
