Patricia Busher, principal of Cleveland Elementary School in Stockton,
CA, where camouflage-garbed Patrick Purdy killed five children and
wounded 30 with an AK-47 on Tuesday, spoke in words translated into
Cambodian at a memorial service Saturday for the four slain Cambodian
children. She said the senseless tragedy could have happened anywhere
and the worst pain would go away in time. A Catholic mass was held for
the Vietnamese victim. Governor Deukmejian planned to speak at a
service Monday. Purdy, who had attended Cleveland Elementary, also
killed himself. He was buried Friday in an unmarked grave. Purdy's
mother remained unlocated, listing a chemical shed as her
address.</SUM>
